From: Galileo CSM Workspace <galileo-csm@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 00:00:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] BaseTools: accept ucs_2 codec name

Python 3.9 and newer look up the custom UCS-2 codec as ucs_2 instead of
ucs-2. Accept both spellings so BaseTools can run on current Python 3 hosts.

This mirrors the small upstream compatibility fix that landed after this
baseline.
---
 BaseTools/Source/Python/AutoGen/UniClassObject.py | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/BaseTools/Source/Python/AutoGen/UniClassObject.py b/BaseTools/Source/Python/AutoGen/UniClassObject.py
index 9f6a271566..9bd131b1bd 100644
--- a/BaseTools/Source/Python/AutoGen/UniClassObject.py
+++ b/BaseTools/Source/Python/AutoGen/UniClassObject.py
@@ -152,7 +152,7 @@ class Ucs2Codec(codecs.Codec):
 
 TheUcs2Codec = Ucs2Codec()
 def Ucs2Search(name):
-    if name == 'ucs-2':
+    if name in ['ucs-2', 'ucs_2']:
         return codecs.CodecInfo(
             name=name,
             encode=TheUcs2Codec.encode,
